metadata.title: Degenerative and Reduction Processes in Chum Juveniles Olfactory Epithelium (Oncorhynchus keta Walbaum: Salmoniformes) at Acute Effect of Copper and Zinc Salts
metadata.description: Electronic microscope research of chum juveniles olfactory epithelium is conducted before and after effect of copper and zinc salts. Some singularities destruction and recovery of olfactory epithelium cells are circumscribed. Information about terms of regeneration of the cells separate types are adduced.
metadata.notes:
Purpose: Research of influence of copper salts (concentration 30 mkg/l, 60 mkg/l, 190 mkg/l) and zinc (concentration 100 mkg/l) on olfactory epithelium juvenile of chum salmon.

Status: Complete
